Let’s be real, the best part of baking cookies is eating the cookie dough, which is why I just loooove these Cookie dough truffles! 

I have been making these for years, and they are a treat I like having on hand in the freezer, like emergency cookie dough 😁

RECIPE 
Ingredients 
- 1/2 cup butter
- 1/3 cup brown sugar
- 1/4 cup granulated sugar
- 1/2 tsp salt
- 1 tsp vanilla
- 1 tbsp milk
- 1 1/4 cup flour, see note*
- 1/2 cup mini chocolate chips
- 1/2 cup dark molding chocolate (optional)
- 1/2 cup light molding chocolate (optional)

Ingredients
1. Add butter and sugars to a bowl and using a hand mixer cream together for 2-3 minutes 
2. Add salt, vanilla, milk and heat treated flour to the bowl and mix again until combined. The mixture will look crumbly in texture. 
3. Using a silicone spatula, stir in you chocolate chips
4. Scoop out cookie dough using a small cookie scoop, or about 2 tsp with a regular spoon and roll into balls. You may need to gently squeeze the dough together before rolling into a ball 
5. Place on a parchment lined cookie sheet and place in the freezer for 10 mins 
6. While the cookie dough balls are in the freezer, melt the molding wafers in the microwave or over a double boiler 
7. Remove cookie dough balls from the freezer and dip them into the melted chocolate. Using a fork place the balls back onto the cookie sheet 
8. If desired, drizzle additional chocolate on top or roll balls into sprinkles (or whatever you like really).
9. Place in the fridge for at least 15 mins to allow the chocolate to harden, then enjoy! 

Note:

Make sure to heat treat the flour before to kill off any bacteria. This can be done in the oven by spreading out the flour on a parchment-lined baking sheet and baking the flour for 5-10 mins at 350 degrees F

Alternatively, you can place the flour in a microwave safe bowl and heat in 30 second increments, and stirring in between in between increments. Do this 4-5 times to properly heat treat the flour
#cookiedough #ediblecookiedough #cookiedoughbites #cookiedoughtruffles #truffles

Ready for the ultimate comfort food?! 🍗 Here are my tips for the crispy, crunchy buttermilk fried chicken!

Ingredients
* 8 bone-in, skin-on chicken thighs and/or drums
* Canola oil for frying
Spice blend
* 1 1/2 tbs Kosher salt
* 2 tsp Freshly ground black pepper
* 1 1/2 tbs Paprika
* 1 tbs Garlic powder
* 1 tbs Onion Powder
* 1-2 tsp Cayenne Powder
Buttermilk Brine
* 1 1/2 cups Buttermilk
* 2-3 tbs spice blend
* 1 egg
* 2 tbs pickle brine (optional)
Flour coating
* 1 1/2 cups all-purpose flour
* 1/2 corn starch
* 1 tsp baking powder
* Reserved spice blend, be about 3-4 tbs
Instructions
1. Combine all seasonings listed in the spice blend in a small bowl and set aside.
2. In a large bowl, combine the buttermilk, 2-3 tablespoon of the spice blend, egg and pickle brine, if using. Whisk to combine.
3. Fully submerge the chicken in the buttermilk mixture. 
4. Cover the bowl with plastic wrap or a lid and refrigerate for at least 4 hours, ideally overnight for the best flavour.
5. When ready to fry, combine the flour, corn starch, baking powder and the remaining spice blend. Mix well.
6. Add 2-3 tablespoons of the marinade from the bowl of the marinating chicken into the flour mixture and work it into the flour with your fingertips.
7. Remove chicken thighs from the buttermilk marinade and allow the excess to drip off.
8. Dredge each piece of chicken in the seasoned flour mixture, pressing the flour onto the chicken.
9. Place the coated chicken on a wire rack or a plate and let it sit for 10-15 minutes as this helps the coating adhere better.
10. While the chicken is resting, heat canola oil in a large, deep skillet or Dutch oven to 350°F degrees. I highly recommend a candy thermometer.
11. Add chicken to the hot oil, skin side down. Do not overcrowd the pan; fry in batches.
12. Fry for about 10-15 minutes, depending on the size of the chicken and flip halfway until the chicken is golden brown and the internal temperature reaches 165°F degrees.
13. Use tongs to remove the chicken from the oil and place it on clean wire rack or a paper towel-lined plate to drain any excess oil.
14. If you like, season with salt to taste and enjoy!

Soup season is upon us! And we are starting off strong with tomato soup 🍅🥫

RECIPE 
Ingredients
* 3 pounds of fresh tomatoes (I like a blend of heirloom, roma and cherry tomatoes), quartered
* 1 red pepper, large slices
* 1 medium onion, quartered
* 1 bulb of garlic, halved
* 5-8 sprigs of fresh thyme
* 1/4 cup of extra virgin olive oil
* Kosher salt to taste
* Freshly ground black pepper
* 1/2 cup basil, roughly chopped
* 2 cups of vegetable broth
* 1 tsp smoked paprika
* 1-2 tbsp brown sugar, to taste
* 1/2 cup of heavy cream
Instructions
1. Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F
2. Wash and chop the tomatoes and red pepper
3. Cut the onion into quarters and cut the garlic bulb in half
4. Place all the veggies onto a parchment lined cookie sheet and drizzle olive oil over the veggie mixture
5. Add salt and pepper along with the fresh thyme and give the veggies a mix with your hands
6. Roast in the oven for 40-45 mins, till caramelized
7. Once cool enough to handle, strip the thyme off the woody stems, squeeze the garlic out of the bulb halves and place everything into a blender
8. Add fresh basil, vegetable broth, smoked paprika, and brown sugar to taste. Blend till smooth
9. Pour the soup into a pot to warm back up on medium heat
10. Add the heavy cream and season with more salt and pepper to taste
11. Serve with an extra drizzle of cream, fresh basil or basil oil. Enjoy!
#tomatosoup #roastedtomatosoup #tomatorecipes #tomatoseason #soupseason

If you’re anything like me you are swimming in end of summer tomatoes. 🍅 Let me show you how to can your own crushed tomatoes, perfect for pasta sauce, soups, stews and chilli! 

Ingredients
* Plum or Roma tomatoes
* Salt
* Fresh basil

Instructions
1. The night before, wash your canning jars in hot soapy water or in the dishwasher.
2. Place the lids and rings in heat proof bowl and pour boiling water over them to sterilize.
3. When ready, wash tomatoes thoroughly in cold water.
4. Cut off the stem, halve the tomatoes and gently squeeze out the seeds. Discard the seeds.
5. Once you have enough de-seeded tomatoes you can start the canning process.
6. Add 1/4 tsp of salt to the bottom of your clean jar along with 2-3 basil leaves.
7. Add your tomatoes to the jar, about half way.
8. Using the handle of a wooden spoon, crush the tomatoes in the jar to remove air bubbles and pack the tomatoes tightly.
9. Repeat this process till you filled the jar leaving about a 1/2-inch of headspace.
10. Add a couple more basil leaves to the top if you like then wipe the rim of the jar with a clean damp cloth or paper towel.
11. Place a lid and ring to the top of your jar and screw on the lid till finger-tight.
12. Place the jars into a stock pot and fill with water ensuring the jars are fully submerged with at least an inch of water covering them.
13. Add in at least one potato, which is used to gauge when the jars are done boiling.
14. Bring the water to a boil and let the jars boil until the potato is fork tender. This can take anywhere from 35 to 90 minutes depending on your size of stock pot and how many jars you are processing.
15. Once jars have boiled long enough, carefully remove the jars from the pot and place them on a clean towel to cool for 12-24 hours.
16. Once cooled completely, check the seals by pressing down on the center of each lid.
17. If the lid pops back up, the jar is not sealed properly, so refrigerate and use that jar within a 3-4 days.
18. Label the sealed jars and store them in a cool, dark and dry place and you can enjoy your summer tomatoes all year long!
#canning #canningtomatoes #summertomatoes

You might think pineapple doesn’t belong on pizza, but pineapple definitely belongs in your pizza oven! 

This Brazilian BBQ grilled pineapple is the perfect dessert to make in the New @Oonihq Karu 12G. With new features, like the built-in ambient temperature thermometer, you can ensure a perfect cook and bake, every time! If you’d like to learn more, check the link on my profile! 

RECIPE:
Ingredients
* 1 pineapple, cored and cut into wedges
* 1 cup brown sugar
* 2 tsp cinnamon
* 1/2 tsp ground ginger
* 1/4 tsp salt
Instructions
1. Combine brown sugar, cinnamon, ginger and salt in a small bowl.
2. Transfer the cinnamon sugar mixture to a large resealable plastic bag, add in the pineapple wedges and shake well to coat each wedge of pineapple.
3. Let marinate for 15 minutes in the fridge. In the meantime, fire up your oven and aim for 570 degree F on the pizza stone.
4. Once the oven is ready, place your grill pan into the oven to preheat for 5 minutes.
5. Add a drizzle of oil to the pan then carefully lay the pineapple wedges onto the grill pan.
6. Turn the flame of the oven to medium low to prevent burning the sugar and cook the pineapple for 3-4 minutes on each side until heated through.
7. Serve warm with a scoop of vanilla ice cream and caramel sauce, it’s a must, and enjoy!

I was not ready for summer to be over but the only thing that got me excited for Fall was all the pumpkin! Like this pumpkin and cream cheese loaf! The cream cheese is layered right into the loaf and it’s topped with the most amazing pecan streusel! 
This load really has everything! Recipe below! 
Pecan Streusel
* 1/2 cup (60g) All purpose flour
* 1/4 cup (50g) brown sugar, packed
* 1/2 tsp cinnamon
* 1/4 cup chopped pecans
* 1/4 cup butter, melted (salted or unsalted)
Cream Cheese filling
* 1/2 (125g) a package of cream cheese, room temperature
* 1/4 cup (50g) granulated sugar
* 1 egg yolk
* 1 tsp vanilla
* 1 tbs (8g) all purpose flour
Pumkin loaf
* 1 cup (250ml) pumpkin puree
* 1 large egg
* 1/2 cup (100g) brown sugar, packed
* 1/4 cup (50g) granulated sugar
* 1/4 cup (60ml) sour cream
* 1/4 cup (60ml) vegetable or canola oil
* 2 tsp vanilla extract
* 1 1/2 cup (180g) all purpose flour
* 1 tsp baking powder
* 1/2 tsp baking soda
* 1/4 tsp salt
* 3 tsp pumpkin pie spice
Instructions
1. In a small bowl, combine flour, brown sugar, cinnamon and pecans
2. Pour the melted butter over the mixture and combine with a fork until the mixture is crumbly in texture. Set aside.
3. In another small bowl, add the cream cheese and using a hand mixer, beat the cream cheese till smooth
4. Add the sugar, egg yolk, vanilla and flour to the cream cheese and blend again till smooth. Set aside.
5. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F. Line a 9x5 loaf pan with parchment paper. Allow the parchment to overhang in the pan. Set aside.
6. Add the pumpkin puree, egg, sugars, sour cream, oil and vanilla to a large bowl. Whisk till smooth and combined.
7. Add in your flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and pumpkin pie spice to the wet ingredients and use a spatula to mix together till combined. Do not over-mix.
8. Pour half of the pumpkin mixture into the prepared loaf pan and using a spatula smooth the mixture into the pan
9. Pour the cream cheese mixture over the pumpkin mixture and smooth gently trying to keep the mixture in the centre of the pan. Rest of Recipe is in the comments #pumpkinloaf #pumpkinlover #creamcheesepumpkinbread #pumpkinquickbread

Tomato and Potato Salad is a simple, but don’t let it fool you. It is so flavourful! Personally, it’s very nostalgic for me! My mother would make this for us after a long day of canning tomatoes, so that potato didn’t go to waste, (work smarter not harder, am I right?) but if I am being totally honest I make this as a side dish all the time! It’s one of my personal faves. 

Ingredients
* 2 medium-sized potatoes
* 3 Roma tomatoes, sliced
* 1 small red onion, sliced
* 3-4 tbs of extra-virgin olive oil
* 1 tsp kosher salt, more to taste
* 1/2 tsp dried oregano
* Freshly ground black pepper, to taste
Instructions
1. Place the whole potatoes in a large pot and cover them with cold water
2. Add a pinch of salt to the water to enhance the potato flavour and bring the water to a boil.
3. Let the potatoes simmer for about 20-25 minutes, or until they are fork-tender.
4. Remove the boiled potatoes from the pot and allow them to cool enough to handle, then gently peel the potatoes using a knife or your fingers.
5. Slice the peeled potatoes into wedges and transfer them to a large mixing bowl.
6. Add the sliced tomatoes and red onion to the bowl with the sliced potatoes.
7. In a small bowl, combine the extra-virgin olive oil, salt, black pepper and dried oregano. Whisk the dressing until well combined.
8. Drizzle the olive oil mixture over the potato and tomato salad and gently toss to coat all the ingredients evenly with the dressing.
9. Taste and adjust the seasonings to your liking.
10. Let the salad sit for about 5-10 minutes before serving. This allows the flavours to meld together.
11. Enjoy!
#potatosalad #tomatosalad #saladrecipe #freshsalad #simplesalad

Cream cheese swirled in the middle ✅
Topped with a Pecan streusel ✅
I promise, this will be the last pumpkin loaf recipe you will need!
Ingredients
Pecan Streusel
* 1/2 cup (60g) All purpose flour
* 1/4 cup (50g) brown sugar, packed
* 1/2 tsp cinnamon
* 1/4 cup chopped pecans
* 1/4 cup butter, melted (salted or unsalted)
Cream Cheese filling
* 1/2 (125g) a package of cream cheese, room temperature
* 1/4 cup (50g) granulated sugar
* 1 egg yolk
* 1 tsp vanilla
* 1 tbs (8g) all purpose flour
Pumkin loaf
* 1 cup (250ml) pumpkin puree
* 1 large egg
* 1/2 cup (100g) brown sugar, packed
* 1/4 cup (50g) granulated sugar
* 1/4 cup (60ml) sour cream
* 1/4 cup (60ml) grape seed, vegetable or canola oil
* 2 tsp vanilla extract
* 1 1/2 cup (180g) all purpose flour
* 1 tsp baking powder
* 1/2 tsp baking soda
* 1/4 tsp salt
* 3 tsp pumpkin pie spice
Instructions
1. In a small bowl, combine flour, brown sugar, cinnamon and pecans
2. Pour the melted butter over the mixture and combine with a fork until the mixture is crumbly in texture. Set aside.
3. In another small bowl, add the cream cheese and using a hand mixer, beat the cream cheese till smooth
4. Add the sugar, egg yolk, vanilla and flour to the cream cheese and blend again till smooth. Set aside.
5. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F. Line a 9x5 loaf pan with parchment paper. Allow the parchment to overhang in the pan. Set aside.
6. Add the pumpkin puree, egg, sugars, sour cream, oil and vanilla to a large bowl. Whisk till smooth and combined.
7. Add in your flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and pumpkin pie spice to the wet ingredients and use a spatula to mix together till combined. Do not over-mix.

10. Add the rest of the pumpkin mixture on top of the cream cheese mixture and smooth gently with a spatula. Try your best not to disturb the cheese cake layer.

Pizza night just got an upgrade!! I am sharing my caramelized onion pizza recipe that is one of my family’s favourite recipes and about to become a family favourite of yours as well! 
Pizzas were baked in the new @oonihq Karu 12G—click the link in my bio to learn more and let’s #MakePizza!! 🍕 #gifted 

RECIPE:
Ingredients
* 1 - 250-gram Classic Pizza dough balls
* 1 tsp Olive oil
* 4 tsp caramelized onions, divided
* 1/4 cup pizza mozzarella, shredded
* 1/4 cup fontina cheese, shredded
* Grated Parmigiano Reggiano, for garnish
* Parsley, finely chopped for garnish
* Red pepper flakes, for garnish (optional)
Instructions
1. Fire up your Ooni oven allowing it to preheat for 15-20 mins. Aim for 850-950 degrees F on your baking stone.
2. On a lightly floured surface, stretch out the pizza dough into a round shape.
3. Transfer the stretched dough to a pizza peel or a wooden board dusted with cornmeal or flour to prevent sticking.
4. Drizzle and spread your olive oil all over the pizza dough leaving a small border around the edges for the crust.
5. Add about 3 teaspoons of the caramelized onions evenly over the pizza dough, followed by the shredded mozzarella and fontina cheese.
6. Carefully launch the pizza into the preheated pizza oven stone and cook for 1-2 minutes, turning every 20 seconds to ensure an even bake.
7. Once the pizza is done, remove it from the oven using a pizza peel and garnish with about a teaspoon or more of caramelized onions, Parmigiano Reggiano and parsley. If you like a little heat, sprinkle on some red pepper flakes as well.
8. Allow the pizza to cool slightly before slicing and serving. Enjoy!

These are the BEST Brown Butter Chocolate Chip Cookies ever and have a secret ingredient. Milk powder! Which takes these cookies to a whole other level! 
Ingredients
* 1 stick or 1/2 cup (113g) unsalted butter, divided
* 2 tbs milk powder
* 2/3 cup (133g) dark brown sugar, packed
* 1/4 cup (50g) granulated sugar
* 1 egg, room temperature
* 2 tsp vanila extract
* 1 1/2 cup (180g) all purpose flour
* 1/2 tsp baking soda
* 1/2 tsp kosher salt
* 1 cup (240g) semi-sweet chocolate chips or chopped dark chocolate, plus more for on top
* Flaky salt (optional)
Instructions
1. Add 85g or three quarters of the stick of butter to a small saucepan over medium heat. Leave the reserved tablespoon of butter aside.
2. Once the butter is melted add in the milk powder.
3. Stir constantly until the butter begins to foam, turns golden brown and smells nutty. Remove from heat.
4. Add in the reserved butter and allow the butter to cool.
5. In the bowl of a stand mixer with the paddle attachment or with a hand mixer, beat the butter and sugars until they are light and creamy, about 2 minutes.
6. Add the egg and vanilla and beat again for another 2 minutes.
7. In a separate bowl, whisk together the flour, baking soda and salt.
8. Add about half of the flour mixture and mix till just combined with a spatula or on low speed in the stand mixer.
9. Add the other half of the flour mixture and the chocolate chips. Mix and fold with a spatula or on low in a stand mixer. Make sure not to over mix!
10. Refrigerate for at least 1 hour, ideally 24 hours. These can be refrigerated up to 72 hours.
11. When ready to bake, preheat your oven to 350 degrees F and line your cookie sheet with parchment paper and set aside.
12. If the dough refrigerated for longer than an hour, let dough sit at room temperature, about 15-20 minutes to allow the dough to slightly soften.
13. Scoop out your cookies using a 2oz scoop and place the dough balls on the prepared cookie sheet, about 3 inches apart. Add more chocolate chips or chunks on top, if you’d like. #brownbuttercookies #brownbutterchocolatechipcookies #chocolatechipcookies

What’s better than a Snickers bar? Snickers bars stuffing onto a blondie cookie bar! So let’s put that left over candy to good use shall we! 

Ingredients
* 1/2 cup (1 stick or 113g) unsalted butter, melted then cooled
* 1 cup (200g) brown sugar, packed
* 1 egg
* 2 tsp vanilla extract
* 1 cup (120g) All purpose flour
* 1/4 tsp baking powder
* 1/4 tsp kosher salt
* 1/8 tsp baking soda
* 1 cup of halloween candy, chopped and divided
Instructions
1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F and line and 8-inch square pan with parchment paper. Set aside.
2. In a medium bowl, whisk together the butter, sugar, egg and vanilla till pale in colour, about 2 minutes.
3. Add in the flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda. Stir till just combined. Don’t over mix!
4. Fold in 1/2 cup of the halloween candy, then spread batter evenly into the prepared pan.
5. Add the rest of the candy bar pieces on top of the batter and bake for 25-30 minutes or until a skewer comes out clean from the centre.
6. Allow to cool in the pan for 15-20 mins before slicing and enjoy!

Do you love roasted garlic, but don’t love the roasting time? Then you need to start roasting garlic in the air fryer! It takes about half the time and gives you the same creamy texture in about 25 minutes! 

Whenever I need roasted garlic fast, this is my go-to! 

Ingredients
* One head of garlic
* 1 tsp extra-virgin olive oil
* Salt and pepper, to taste

Instructions
1. Preheat the air fryer to 390 degrees F for 3-5 minutes.
2. While the air fryer warms up, cut the top off the head of the garlic and place in a piece of foil.
3. Pour the olive oil over the top of the cut garlic and season with salt and pepper.
4. Wrap the foil around the garlic to create a pouch and place in the pre-warmed air fryer
5. Air fry for 23-25 minutes, until the garlic is soft.
6. Allow the garlic to rest in the foil for 10-15 mins to cool slightly.
7. Open the foil pouch carefully to allow the steam to escape and to further cool.
8. Enjoy!
#AirFryerRecipes #AirFryerHacks #RoastedGarlic #RoastedGarlicRecipe

If you’re anything like me, you love a quick weekday meal. This Tuscan chicken pasta is just the thing! Prepare for this to be on a weekly rotation. 

Ingredients
Chicken
* 1/2 tsp kosher salt
* 1/2 tsp freshly ground black pepper
* 1/2 tsp paprika
* 1/4 tsp oregano
* 1/4 tsp garlic powder
* 2 chicken breasts
* 2-3 tsp olive oil, enough to lightly coat chicken
Tuscan Pasta
* 450g penne or rigatoni
* 3/4 cup of pancetta or thick-cut bacon, diced
* 2 tbs of butter
* 1 medium onion, finely chopped
* 1 red bell pepper, diced
* 4 cloves of garlic, finely chopped
* 3 tbsp tomato paste
* 1 cup chicken stock
* 2 cups heavy cream
* 1/4 tsp dried basil
* 1/4 tsp dried oregano
* 1/4 tsp dried rosemary
* 1/4 tsp dried thyme
* 1 tsp chili pepper flakes
* Salt and pepper, to taste
* 1 cup freshly grated Parmigiano Reggiano, plus more for garnish
* 1/2 cup Sun-dried tomatoes in oil, roughly chopped
* 3 cups baby spinach, roughly chopped
* Italian parsley, chopped for garnish
Instructions
1. Combine the salt, black pepper, paprika, oregano and garlic powder in a small bowl. Set aside.
2. Pat your chicken breast dry with paper towel and drizzle on the olive oil.
3. Sprinkle the seasoning blend on both sides of the chicken and coat evenly.
4. Air fry the chicken at 380 degrees for 10-15 minutes or until the internal temperature of the chicken reaches 165 degrees. Flip half way.
5. Once fully cooked set aside to let rest.
6. Bring water to boil in a large pot.
7. Once boiling, salt the water. It should taste like a very well seasoned broth.
8. Add your pasta to the boiling water and cook as per the package directions. Don’t forget to keep some of your pasta water!
9. While the pasta is cooking, heat a large skillet over medium heat.
10. Add the pancetta to the skillet and brown for 6-8 minutes. Remove the crispy pancetta leaving the rendered fat in the pan.
11. Add your butter to the pan along with the onion and red pepper. Cook till soft and translucent, 5-8 minutes.
12. Add in the garlic and cook till fragrant, about a minute, then add in your tomato paste and cook for another 2-4 minutes till the tomato paste deepens in colour.

Anything wrapped in puff pastry is a big YES fa me! These ham and swiss puff pastries are perfect for breakfast, brunch, a snack, or as an app during this holiday season! 

Ingredients
* 2 tbsp Dijon mustard
* 5 Ham slices, any kind
* 5 Swiss cheese slices or Cheddar cheese slices
* 1 sheet of puff pastry
* Egg wash
* Everything Bagel seasoning or sesame seeds
Instructions
1. Preheat oven to 375 degrees and line a cookie sheet with parchment paper. Set aside.
2. Unroll your puff pastry and roll out the dough to thin and flatten.
3. Cut the sheet of pastry into 9 equal rectangles and place on the prepared cookie sheet.
4. Add about 1/2 teaspoon of mustard to the puff pastry. Feel free to add more if you like.
5. Take the cheese slices and cut them in half. Take the halves and cut them lengthwise again into strips.
6. Do the same with the ham slices.
7. Layer the cheese then the ham overtop of the Dijon mustard.
8. Using some of the egg wash wet the inside of one edge of the pastry.
9. Fold the dry edge over the ham and cheese then place the wet edge overtop. Lightly press to seal.
10. Brush the top of the pastry with egg wash and sprinkle on some Everything bagel seasoning or sesame seeds .
11. Bake for 25-28 minutes, and lightly golden
12. Cool on the cookie sheet for 2-3 minutes then they are ready to serve and enjoy!

Shortbread is a holiday must! Don’t let this simple biscuit fool you, they are buttery, melt in your mouth and necessary for your cookie boxes! 

Ingredients 
- 1 cup plus 2 tbsp (250 g) European butter, room temperature
- 1/2 tsp vanilla (optional)
- 1/2 tsp kosher salt
- 1/2 cup plus 2 tbsp (125 g) granulated sugar
- 3 cups (360 g) all purpose flour
- 2 tbs (16g) corn starch
- Sanding or coarse sugar for on top

Instructions
1. Pre-heat your oven to 325 degrees F and line a 8x8 square tray with parchment paper. 
2. Using a stand mixer with a paddle attachment  or a hand mixer, add in the butter, vanilla, salt and sugar into a bowl and beat on medium-high speed till creamed and smooth, about 2-3 minutes.
3. In a large bowl, sift flour and corn starch together. 
4. Add the flour mixture into the butter mixture in thirds and mix on low to incorporate together. Do this two more times. 
5. Increase the speed to medium and beat until the dough comes together.
6. Press the dough into the prepared baking pan and dock the surface with a skewer or fork and top with a generous amount of sanding sugar
7. Bake for 40-45 mins or until slightly golden on top with lightly brown edges 
8. Remove from the oven and place the pan on a cooling rack. Allow the shortbread to cool for 10 minutes.
9. After the 10 minutes the shortbread will still be a little warm, remove from the pan and cut the shortbread into little bars.
10. If you want the holes to be more pronounced, now would be the time to re-poke the dough as well. 
11. Place the cut cookies back on the cooling rack till the cookies are cooled completely and enjoy!

Want bakery style muffins every time? Use these 4 tips to guarantee super-domed muffins! ⬇️
1️⃣ Once your batter is mixed, let it rest for 45 minutes to allow the leaveners to active resulting in sky-high muffin tops
2️⃣ Use every other muffin well. This allows heat to penetrate on all sides of batter which will help them muffins rise 
3️⃣ Fill each well to the very tippy top so you get those perfect muffin tops that spill over onto the tin. These aren’t cupcakes, so no flat tops here! 
4️⃣Bake at 425 degrees F (NOT 475! 🙃) for 6-8 minutes to super charge the leaveners creating tons of rise. Then without opening the oven door, drop the temperature to 350 degrees F and continue baking for 8-10 minutes. 

Did I miss any other tips? Let me know your go-to’s and here’s to no more flat top muffins! 
#muffins #bakingtips

Timmie’s getting rid of the OG Chocolate chip muffin is my Roman Empire. RECIPE⬇️

Ingredients
* 2 1/2 cups (300g)all purpose flour
* 1 cup (200g) granulated sugar
* 2 tsp baking powder
* 1/2 tsp baking soda
* 1/2 tsp salt
* 1 1/2 cups mini chocolate chips, divided
* 2 eggs, room temperature
* 1/3 cup (68g) unsalted butter, melted and cooled
* 1/4 cup (60g) vegetable oil
* 3/4 cup (190g) buttermilk
* 1/3 cup (60g) Greek yogurt, 2% or higher or full fat sour cream
* 1 tbsp vanilla extract
* 2-3 tbsp coarse or turbinado sugar, for sprinkling
Instructions
1. Whisk the flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt and 1 1/4 cup chocolate chips together in a large bowl.
2. In a medium bowl, whisk together the eggs, cooled butter, oil, buttermilk and Greek yogurt until smooth and combined.
3. Pour the wet ingredients into the large bowl of dry ingredients and whisk gently till just combined. Be careful not to over-mix.
4. Cover the bowl and let batter rest for 45 minutes. In the meantime, line a muffin tin with 12 paper liners and set aside.
5. Once the 45 minutes is up, preheat your oven to 425 degrees F.
6. Using a large ice cream scoop, divide the batter evenly into each lined muffin tin, slightly overfilling each liner. Try not to disturb the batter too much when scooping.
7. Top each muffin with the reserved chocolate chips and coarse sugar before placing in the oven.
8. Bake at 425 degrees F for 8 minutes, then with keeping the oven door closed, lower the temperature to 350 degrees F for 8-10 minutes.
9. Muffins are done baking when a toothpick comes out clean after being inserted into the center of the muffin.
10. Remove from the oven and let them cool for 5-10 mins in the pan before transferring to a cooling rack for another 5-10 minutes.
11. These are best served warm. Enjoy!
